
[1]serious

   SE'RIOUS, a. [L. serius.]

   1. Grave in manner or disposition; solemn; not light, gay or volatile;
   as a serious man; a serious habit or disposition.

   2. Really intending what is said; being in earnest; not jesting or
   making false pretense. Are you serious, or in jest?

   3. Important; weighty; not trijling.

   The holy Sciptures bring to your ears the most serious things in the
   world. Young.
